\{a_n\}_{n=1}^\infty
a_n= \sum_{i=n}^\infty (-1)^{i-n} \dfrac{1}{i}
a_n
a_n = \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{(-1)^k}{n+k},
\begin{align} a_n - a_{n+1} &= \sum_{k=0}^\infty (-1)^k\left(\frac{1}{n+k} - \frac{1}{n+1+k}\right)\\ &= \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{(-1)^k}{(n+k)(n+1+k)}\\ &> \frac{1}{n(n+1)} - \frac{1}{(n+1)(n+2)}\\ &> 0, \end{align}
\dfrac{1}{(n+k)(n+1+k)}
